<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9788: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-30T19:00:00-04:00">August 30, 1937—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>195. Your 561, August 30, 2 p.m., has been repeated to Tokyo for
                                communication by the Ambassador to his interested colleagues. The
                                Ambassador has been authorized to associate himself with them in
                                appropriate representations to the Japanese Government.<note n="85" xml:id="d559fn85">See <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of
                                    September 1, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_494"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941,
                                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 494</ref>.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>